<main>

JAMAICA COFFEE HOUSE

P: So you pieced together Jamaica Coffee House. That’s where I’m heading today. And as you took the time to crack that code, I think I can trust you now. 

You wanted to know the reason I’m here? I have a wider project in this city, and it is to get a deeper understanding of this frankly tyrannical institution of slavery, and where better to do that than the place where all the English men with power over the empire meet to socialise? I also think that… and shh, I can’t say this too loudly. I think that the more that I understand this institution… and the more people I meet and win over to my side here, the more likely I can secure my freedom back home. 

I can’t say much more now. But, I think I can trust you. So do you want to come with me to the Jamaica Coffee House? I’ll teach you some things along the way, to pass the time - and anybody who sees us will think we are simply doing some lovely creative writing exercises across time zones together. Great. Let’s go.

