But shh. As I said, I can’t talk so explicitly. So let’s talk about secrets, and do another little creative writing session - in case anybody is watching.

Back home with my mother in West Africa, I used to speak a language called Wolof. Now, in Boston and London, I’m not able to speak my mother-tongue - people would see it as defiant, disobedient. But I made sure I remembered some words, and sometimes I write secretly in my mother-tongue. Try and guess the words to uncover their meanings.

"At night, in my dreams… my <strong>yaay</strong> opens her arms wide to <strong>merhbe</strong> me home. She tells me to <strong>taxawal</strong> my tears because everything will be alright" 

